As per SEBI\'s new peak margin rules, 20％ of the value of stocks sold from your portfolio will be blocked for trading on the day you\'ve sold them (T Day).

This blocked margin will be available from the next trading day (T+1).
As per regulations, funds from selling Unsettled & Unpaid Holdings will not be available for further trades on the same day and hence, blocked. The funds will be released tomorrow.

As per SEBI\'s peak margin regulations, profits earned on T day (trading day) will be blocked and cannot be used for further trading/investing.

FnO profits will be available to trade from T+1 day and Equity profits are available from T+2 days.

Good Till Trigger (GTT) Order is a feature that allows you to buy or sell scrips at your desired price with 1 year expiry date. 

You have to set a Trigger Price in GTT order and if the LTP hits the Trigger Price, the order gets released to the exchange for execution.

GTT has the product type as Delivery and Margin in the Equity Cash segment on NSE & BSE and Carry-Forward type orders in the Derivatives segment on NSE, MCX & NCDEX.
